title: Tajikistan Exports
description:
Exports in Tajikistan decreased to 143.20 USD Million in July from 367 USD Million in June of 2022. Exports in Tajikistan averaged 96.58 USD Million from 2000 until 2022, reaching an all time high of 431.10 USD Million in March of 2021 and a record low of 35.10 USD Million in October of 2014. In Tajikistan, aluminium and cotton account for over 75 percent of exports. Electricity is the third most important export, a by-product of the country’s hydroelectric dams. Tajikistan’s main export partners are China, Turkey, Russia, Iran and Afghanistan.
. This page provides the latest reported value for - Tajikistan Exports - plus previous releases, historical high and low, short-term forecast and long-term prediction, economic calendar, survey consensus and news.
author: State Statistical Committee of the Republic of Tajikistan
